Audio To Text
API reference for the audio-to-text pipeline. Accepts audio input and returns a transcript using Whisper-compatible models.

POST

https://livepeer.studio/api/beta/generate
/
audio-to-text

Try it
Authorizations
​
Authorization
stringheaderrequired
Bearer authentication header of the form Bearer <token>, where <token> is your auth token.

Body
multipart/form-data
​
audio
filerequired
Uploaded audio file to be transcribed.

​
model_id
stringdefault:""
Hugging Face model ID used for transcription.

​
return_timestamps
stringdefault:true
Return timestamps for the transcribed text. Supported values: 'sentence', 'word', or a string boolean ('true' or 'false'). Default is 'true' ('sentence'). 'false' means no timestamps. 'word' means word-based timestamps.

​
metadata
stringdefault:{}
Additional job information to be passed to the pipeline.

Response

200

application/json
Successful Response

Response model for text generation.

​
text
stringrequired
The generated text.

​
chunks
Chunk · object[]required
The generated text chunks.

Hide child attributes

​
chunks.timestamp
any[]required
The timestamp of the chunk.

​
chunks.text
stringrequired
The text of the chunk.

const form = new FormData();
form.append('audio', '<string>');
form.append('model_id', '');
form.append('return_timestamps', 'true');
form.append('metadata', '{}');

const options = {method: 'POST', headers: {Authorization: 'Bearer <token>'}};

options.body = form;

fetch('https://livepeer.studio/api/beta/generate/audio-to-text', options)
  .then(res => res.json())
  .then(res => console.log(res))
  .catch(err => console.error(err));

